      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Miami Heat signed first-round draft pick HAROLD MINERto a long-term contract yesterday. Terms weren't disclosed, but published reports said the team's offer was for five years and $7.3 million.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The Miami Heat signed first-round draft pick HAROLD MINERto a long-term contract yesterday. Terms weren't disclosed, but published reports said the team's offer was for five years and $7.3 million.</p>
        <p>Miner, a high-scoring guard from Southern Cal, was the 12th player taken in the June draft. He averaged 23.5 points in his three-year career with the Trojans. (AP)  SPORTS PEOPLE: PRO BASKETBALL</p>
      </block>
